      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera S is an impeccable example of Stuttgart engineering, featuring the 3.8L naturally aspirated flat-six mated to a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. The drivetrain remains tight with zero seepage, benefiting from a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recent borescope inspection confirming pristine cylinder walls. Performance is anchored by Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and a factory-spec limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal lateral grip and chassis composure. Every bushing, synchro, and throttle response feels factory-new. This is a collector-grade chassis with zero deferred maintenance, ready for the most discerning purist.",
